            <who name="Sebastian Werner">info</who>
            <bug_when>2009-11-18 00:18:06 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Oops, what? You are kidding, right?

This would mean to disable the new engine completely. So you are disabling e.g.:

* ARIA
* Native JSON
* Cross domain XHR
* Cross document messaging
* Data URIs
* CSS Outline
* DOM storage
* Selectors API

You could not really think this is the way to go.

If there is a performance problem in IE8 there should be definitely spend time to find another way to fix it. This is basically the wrong signal and way as this disables a lot of stuff we always waited for IE to implement them.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
